cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper focuses on providing an annotated dataset for multimedia/speech processing communities to investigate multimedia retrieval and speech-related tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of annotations for speech turns, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of annotations for scene boundaries, shot boundaries, and interacting speakers, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SD (Sound) respectively.
